      "solution": "N = int(input().strip())\narr = list(map(int, input().split()))\nout = [0] * N\nif N > 0:\n    out[0] = arr[0]\n    for i in range(1, N):\n        out[i] = arr[i] + arr[i - 1]\nprint(\" \".join(map(str, out)))",
      "statement": "You are given a list of integers. Transform the list using a shifting echo rule:\n\nThe first output number is identical to the first input number.\nEach following output number equals the current input number plus the previous input number.\n\nFormally:\nout[0] = in[0]\nout[i] = in[i] + in[i-1]   for i ≥ 1\n\nYour goal is to compute and print the transformed sequence.",
