    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">You are given a list of integers. Transform the list using a shifting echo rule:<br><br>The first output number is identical to the first input number.<br>Each following output number equals the current input number plus the previous input number.<br><br>Formally:<br>out[0] = in[0]<br>out[i] = in[i] + in[i-1]   for i &ge; 1<br><br>Your goal is to compute and print the transformed sequence.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> An integer <var>N</var> &mdash; the number of values.<br><strong>Line 2:</strong> <var>N</var> space‑separated integers.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">Print <var>N</var> integers &mdash; the shifted echo transformation &mdash; space‑separated (no extra spaces or lines).</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; <var>N</var> &le; 20<br>Each integer fits in a signed 32‑bit range.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">1\n7</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">7</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
